      <abstract>
        <variablelist>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>WHAT?</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>
                &openwebui; is a Web-based application that allows you to
                interact with AI models.
              </para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>WHY?</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>
                To understand what &openwebui; is and learn how to use it to
                effectively interact with AI models.
              </para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>EFFORT</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>
                To understand the basics of &openwebui; takes less than 1 hour.
              </para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>REQUIREMENTS</term>
            <listitem>
              <itemizedlist>
                <para>
                  The descriptions and procedures in this article assume that
                  the following points are already fulfilled:
                </para>
                <listitem>
                  <para>
                    You have successfully deployed the &suseai;.
                  </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                  <para>
                    You can access the &openwebui; interface in your Web
                    browser.
                  </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                  <para>
                    Your &openwebui; user account has been created and you have
                    received the login credentials.
                  </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                  <para>
                    You have navigated your Web browser to the URL of your
                    instance of &openwebui; and logged in with your credentials.
                  </para>
                </listitem>
              </itemizedlist>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
